										The word cereal derives from Ceres, the name of the Roman goddess of harvest and 
										agriculture. Cereal is a grass cultivated for the edible components of their 
										composed of the endosperm, germ, and bran. Cereal grains are grown in greater 
										quantities and provide more food energy worldwide than any other type of crop 
										they are therefore staple crops. In their natural form (as in whole grain), they 
