									</div>
									<p>
										Conventional farming is a production system that avoids or largely excludes the use of 
										synthetically produced agricultural inputs like fertilizers, pesticides, growth 
										regulators, live stock feed additives etc.<br/>
										Toxic chemicals, fertilizers, pesticides and other artificial treatment used in 
										the cultivation of modern crops have been proven to be harmful for the human body 
										in the long term.Conventional foods are grown without the use of such harmful chemicals 
